Carrying out the multiplication:

\[
M^2 = \begin{pmatrix}
2 \times 2 + 3 \times 4 & 2 \times 3 + 3 \times 5 \\
4 \times 2 + 5 \times 4 & 4 \times 3 + 5 \times 5
\end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
4 + 12 & 6 + 15 \\
8 + 20 & 12 + 25
\end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
16 & 21 \\
28 & 37
\end{pmatrix}
\]

The result is \( M^2 = \begin{pmatrix} 16 & 21 \\ 28 & 37 \end{pmatrix} \).

